  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_joint_registry">National Joint Registry</xref>
 is an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_joint_registry">National Joint Registry</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_joint_registry">NJR</xref>
) is managed by the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_healthcare_quality_improvement_partnership">Healthcare Quality Improvement Partnership</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_healthcare_quality_improvement_partnership">HQIP</xref>
).  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_joint_registry">National Joint Registry</xref>
 for England, Wales and Northern Ireland collects information on 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_joint_replacement_surgery">Joint Replacement Surgery</xref>
 and monitors the performance of joint replacement 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_implant">Implants</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
For further information on the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_joint_registry">National Joint Registry</xref>
, see the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_joint_registry">National Joint Registry</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="http://www.njrcentre.org.uk/njrcentre/About-the-NJR"
            scope="external"
            format="html">About the NJR</xref>
.  </p>

